ISP - Internet Service Provider,
Levels of ISP:
  Access - end systems
  Regional//National - access ISPs connect to them (service fees apply)
  T1//Global - regional ISPs connect to them

IXP - Internet Exchange Points - physical infrastructure that allows peering between ISPs of the same level (free of service) [Consists of Network of Switches]

POP - Point Of Presence - physical infrastructure that allows conection between ISPs of different level (service fees apply) [Consists of Routers]

CDN - Content Delivery Network - interconnection of datacenters, allowing for more efficient transmission of content (Commercial)


